{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"7dab66e5-21ec-4524-a77d-33740e184e15","content":"Analyzing .dmp files is outside the scope of the `dump-collect` skill (which only covers *capturing* dumps). However, here's how you can analyze your dump:\n\n**Using `dotnet-dump analyze`** (cross-platform):\n```bash\ndotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\ndotnet-dump analyze <your-file.dmp>\n```\n\nUseful commands inside the analyzer:\n- `clrstack` — managed call stack\n- `pe` — print last exception\n- `dumpheap -stat` — heap summary\n- `threads` — list all threads\n\n**Using LLDB** (Linux/macOS):\n```bash\nlldb --core <your-file.dmp>\nplugin load libsosplugin.so\nclrstack\npe\n```\n\n**Using WinDbg** (Windows):\n```\n.loadby sos coreclr\n!clrstack\n!pe\n```\n\nStart with `pe` (print exception) — it usually points straight to the root cause. Want me to help with a specific step?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"d5669be6-96ba-45d8-a5f1-f654be0b6f58","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about analyzing a .dmp crash dump file. Let me check the available skills - there's a `dump-collect` skill, but its description specifically says \"DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze\". So I should NOT invoke that skill.\n\nI should help the user directly with guidance on analyzing crash dumps.","outputTokens":349,"requestId":"6809:25E777:A82F916:B7790CF:69FD42F7"},"id":"5c1a4fc9-0c3b-4767-8927-ef7ee4bfdee3","timestamp":"2026-05-08T01:57:21.371Z","parentId":"12741904-a7d4-4090-b73e-ed127e2235d7"}
